1 the certified territory of another retail electric supplier, if such
2 extension is necessary for such supplier to connect any of its
3 facilities or to serve its consumers within its own certified
4 territory.
5 B. Except as provided in subsections C and E of this section,
6 any new electric-consuming facility located in an unincorporated
7 area which has not as yet been included in a map issued by the
8 Commission, pursuant to Section 158.24 of this title, or certified,
9 pursuant to Section 158.24 of this title, shall be furnished retail
10 electric service by the retail electric supplier which has an
11 existing distribution line in closer proximity to such electric-
12 consuming facility than is the nearest existing distribution line of
13 any other retail electric supplier. Any disputes under this
14 subsection shall be resolved by the Commission.
15 C. If the Commission, after hearing, shall determine that the
16 retail electric service being furnished or proposed to be furnished
17 by a retail electric supplier to an electric-consuming facility is
18 inadequate and is not likely to be made adequate, the Commission may
19 authorize another retail electric supplier to furnish retail
20 electric service to such facility.
21 D. Except as provided in subsection C of this section, no
22 retail electric supplier shall furnish, make available, render or
23 extend retail electric service to any electric-consuming facility to
24 which such service is being lawfully furnished by another retail
